description:
&lt;p&gt;Do you have a subspecialty interests in: Breast, Chest, GU or Paediatric imaging? An exciting future awaits you at North West Anglia NHS Foundation Trust where patients are at the heart of everything we do.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a friendly, dynamic and innovative group of 13.5 substantive Consultant Radiologists and 2 Locum Radiologists covering all of the major sub-specialities across three acute hospital sites serving a population of 700,000 people.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are keen to promote flexible working to allow for a good work-life balance, this includes opportunities for candidates looking for part time roles but can also offer job plans of 10 PAs plus on call.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Alongside this we offer:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Options for SPAs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Modern facilities and equipment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Possibility of home reporting in the near future&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Trainees via the Eastern Deanery Radiology Training scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Teaching opportunities to the Cambridge University Medical students&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be supported by, and work with, a diverse multi-skilled professional team of clinical and non-clinical friendly staff. London, Stansted and Luton are all within easy travelling distance from our hospitals which are surrounded by areas of outstanding natural beauty.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have two trainees from the Eastern Deanery Radiology Training Scheme and provide weekly Radiology teaching sessions to the Cambridge University medical students on placement.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dr. Tamer Sadek, Consultant Radiologist &amp; Associate Divisional Director – Imaging on 01733 673516 or his PA, Julie Anderson on 01733 673506.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
